ptive and penetrating essays on contemporary philosophical and literary culture. In addition to providing insight into the basic conceptual apparatus of Badiou's philosophy, the essays also offer a more substantial critical assessment of the import of his main theses for different disciplines.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aArea Studies : French Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Theory. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aBeistegui, Miguel de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBosteels, Bruno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrassier, Ray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCopjec, Joan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCritchley, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacCannell, Juliet Flower, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacherey, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMadarasz, Norman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcNulty, Tracy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRabaté, Jean-Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiera, Gabriel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiera, Gabriel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRose, Marilyn Gaddis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2015z978311149061840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079148307740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791483077423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/